[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: icon)\n\nWelcome to Squiggles!  Squiggles.jl is a Julia package to accelerate 1D cross correlations of seismic signals using GPUs! ","category":"section"},{"location":"#Functions","page":"Home","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Squiggles.get_backend","page":"Home","title":"Squiggles.get_backend","text":"get_backend()\n\nReturn the current backend used to perform the calculations.\n\nExample\n\nusing Squiggles\n\nget_backend()\n\nusing Squiggles\nusing CUDA\n\nset_GPUbackend()\n\nget_backend()\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Squiggles.get_available_platforms","page":"Home","title":"Squiggles.get_available_platforms","text":"get_available_platforms()\n\nGet the list of supported platforms that can be used for running the simulations\n\nExample\n\nusing Squiggles\n\nget_available_platforms()\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Squiggles.get_available_GPUplatforms","page":"Home","title":"Squiggles.get_available_GPUplatforms","text":"get_available_GPUplatforms()\n\nGet the list of supported GPU platforms that can be used for running the simulations\n\nExample\n\nusing Squiggles\n\nget_available_GPUplatforms()\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Squiggles.set_CPUbackend","page":"Home","title":"Squiggles.set_CPUbackend","text":"set_CPUbackend()\n\nSet the backend to CPU\n\nExample\n\nusing Squiggles\nusing CUDA\n\nset_CPUbackend()\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Squiggles.set_GPUbackend","page":"Home","title":"Squiggles.set_GPUbackend","text":"set_GPUbackend()\n\nSet the backend to the available GPU.\n\nNotes\n\nThe set backend is decided by the installed packages, i.e. if CUDA.jl is installed (and imported) then CUDA will be used. Only import one JuliaGPU package per script. If no JuliaGPU package is loaded, this method will return a LoadError. See the available GPU platforms by running getavailableGPUplatforms(). Some GPU backends support UnifiedMemory (e.g. CUDA, ROCm, Metal). The default will always be DeviceMemory but users can choose UnifiedMemory by running set_GPUbackend(\"unified\")\n\nExample\n\nusing Squiggles\nusing CUDA\n\nset_GPUbackend()\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
